1952;;The Member of the Wedding;;American;;Fred Zinnemann;;Julie Harris, Ethel Waters;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Member_of_the_Wedding_(film);;Feeling rejected when her older brother goes off on his honeymoon without inviting her along, Frankie (Julie Harris) runs away from her middle-class Southern home. She endures several other adolescent traumas, not least of which is the sudden death of her bespectacled young cousin John Henry (Brandon De Wilde). With the help of warm-hearted housekeeper Berenice Sadie Brown (Ethel Waters), Frankie eventually makes an awkward transition to young womanhood.[2]